\ Text save / load round-trip. `save` writes user vocabulary only
\ (definitions, no values, no stack). `load` re-runs the file as source.

: double 2 * ;
: square dup * ;
variable counter
42 counter !
symbol red
"/tmp/lf_save_test.l4" save

\ Throw away the user vocabulary, including counter's value.
forget double

\ Reload from the saved file — definitions come back, counter's slot
\ exists again but starts uninitialized (no value emitted by save).
"/tmp/lf_save_test.l4" load

\ Definitions work.
8 double .
3 square .
\ Symbol survives.
red .
\ Variable is reachable but its old value was not preserved.
counter @ .
